From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GE-Proton <git@localhost>
Date: Wed, 8 Jul 2026 11:30:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] mmdevapi: Use generic DualSense mono speaker endpoint name.

Spider-Man Remastered can see the active DualSense mono speaker endpoint after
hotplug, but it does not always activate the endpoint when the exposed
interface name is product-specific. The working path matches the controller
speaker through the generic Wireless Controller speaker identity while the
backend still keeps the real Pulse sink/device path and endpoint GUID unique.

Expose the DualSense and DualSense Edge mono speaker interface name as the
generic Wireless Controller speaker. This does not restore the fake PnP
AudioEndpoint registration that caused the main-menu endpoint crash; it only
adjusts the MMDevice friendly/interface names used by applications when
selecting the controller effect speaker.
---
 dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c | 5 +----
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c b/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
index dfe3f2a2664..022da0644e9 100644
--- a/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
+++ b/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
@@ -715,9 +715,7 @@ static const WCHAR *dualsense_mono_endpoint_iname(const WCHAR *device_path)
 {
     if (!device_path)
         return NULL;
-    if (wcsstr(device_path, L"VID_054C&PID_0CE6"))
-        return L"DualSense Wireless Controller Speaker";
-    if (wcsstr(device_path, L"VID_054C&PID_0DF2"))
-        return L"DualSense Edge Wireless Controller Speaker";
+    if (is_dualsense_device_path(device_path))
+        return L"Wireless Controller Speaker";
     return NULL;
 }
